  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6754.42 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma between 6745-6755 (all amplifying strikes), dealers are forced to buy this rally as they're short gamma in a BREAKOUT regime. The recent GEX surge and extreme 1-min/5-min momentum (40.5%/64.5%) suggests dealers are aggressively hedging, creating a feedback loop that should propel price toward the 6775 positive gamma wall where selling pressure will emerge. Watch 6775 as the critical inflection point where dealer flow reverses from buying to selling, while any pullback toward 6745 max negative gamma will trigger more dealer buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect continued upward momentum until 6775 where the rally should stall.",
